cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CE, cs.SD, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper analyzes human mobility data in an urban area using a community bicycle program. 
- cs.CY (Computational Geometry) is also likely as the paper briefly sketches a model for identifying the most probable routes between stations. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is another possible category as the paper uses data mining techniques to preprocess and filter the noisy data. 
- cs.SD (Software Development) is a possible category as the paper proposes an improvement of the Bicing website, including a prediction of the number of available bikes in a certain station within the next minutes/hours. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also a possible category as the paper explores and characterizes data from a community bicycle program, which can have implications for designing better human-computer interfaces for urban mobility.
